1.Make sure git installed in your computer and had set in intelliJ and have GitHub account.
2.In File --> Settings --> GitHUb section, test and apply for connection to your GitHub account.
3.Install .ignore plugin(File --> Settings --> Plugins).
4.VCS --> Enable Version Control Integration... --> Git
5.Right click on Operations project and select New --> .ignore file --> .gitignore file(Git) --> Java --> Generate without duplicates --> Yes
6.Add .idea and *.iml to end of .gitignore file.
7.Open Version Control tab from bottom left.
8.Select all files in Version Control tab, then right click and select Commit...(Or only press Commit button in top right window 's section).
9.Select Unversioned Files and unselect Perform code analysis and fill optional message and then press Commit.(Local Repository)
10.Login to your github account(github.com, abdij2ee:123456jee) and create New repository(Plus sign). Name it Operations.
11.Copy https://github.com/abdij2ee/Operations.git url.
12.Open VCS --> Git --> Remotes... window and paste url.
13.Open VCS --> Git --> Push
14.Refresh https://github.com/abdij2ee/Operations url.
15.Add some code to Main class.
16.Select all files in Version Control tab, then right click and select Commit...(Or only press Commit button in top right window 's section).
17.Select Unversioned Files and unselect Perform code analysis and fill optional message and then press Commit and Push then Push.
18.Refresh https://github.com/abdij2ee/Operations url.